<typeStatus box="[1027,1113,1325,1346]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">holotype</typeStatus>
, I examined 
<specimenCount box="[764,896,1352,1373]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" type="generic">10 specimens</specimenCount>
from: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[966,1065,1352,1373]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">
<collectingCountry box="[966,1061,1352,1373]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">BRAZIL</collectingCountry>
:
</emphasis>
Estado do 
<collectingRegion box="[685,828,1378,1399]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Espirito Santo</collectingRegion>
; Estado do 
<collectingRegion box="[951,1085,1378,1399]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, Mar de Hespanha, J. F. Zikán (
<figureCitation box="[928,1006,1405,1426]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[197,228,1557,1576]" captionTargetBox="[177,1188,196,1539]" captionTargetId="figure-46@15.[175,1190,194,1541]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 48. Geographic distribution of Lasiodera species." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5334330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5334330/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
). Specimens are deposited in BMNH, FMNH, FSCA, MNHN, MRSN, USNM, and WOPC.
</paragraph>
